Explanation2:
\begin{aligned}
I&=\frac{\pi}{2}\left[ \int_{-\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} d x-\int_{-\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} \sin ^{-1} \frac{2 x}{1+x^2} d x \right]\\
&= \frac{\pi}{2}\left[\int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} d x + \int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} d x + \int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} \sin ^{-1} \frac{2 x}{1+x^2} d x + \int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} \sin ^{-1} \frac{-2 x}{1+x^2} d x\right]\\
&=\frac{\pi}{2}\left[\int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} d x + \int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} d x + \int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} \sin ^{-1} \frac{2 x}{1+x^2} d x - \int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} \sin ^{-1} \frac{2 x}{1+x^2} d x\right]\\
&= \frac{\pi}{2}\cdot2\cdot\left[\int_{0}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}} \frac{x^4}{1-x^4} d x\right]
\end{aligned}

